## Definition

For $(\mathcal{C}, \otimes)$ a [[monoidal (âˆž,1)-category]], its **Picard $\infty$-group** is the [[âˆž-group]] induced on the full sub-[[âˆž-groupoid]] $PIC(\mathcal{C}, \otimes)$ on the objects that are invertible under the tensor product. 




